intended_learning_outcomes_of_course.value:
By the end of the course students will be able to:
Demonstrate competence in performing sophisticated queries and updates against an existing RDBMS using most of the advanced features of SQL standard;
Demonstrate skills in designing, writing, changing and testing programs (e.g., Java/JDBC) that use an RDBMS;
Interpret and optimize SQL queries based on the principles of the cost-based query optimization;
Provide an explanation of the database indexing techniques including File Hashing, Search Trees, Multi-level Indexes, B Trees and B+ Trees;
Specify advanced constraints on the DB scheme based on Functional Dependencies & Normalization;
Appreciate Data analytics and aggregation tasks and techniques;
Provide an explanation of the selection selectivity and join selectivity using histograms for query optimization.
